chunk_content: PMTCT (ANC1 Only): Pregnant women tested at their 1st antenatal care clinic (ANC) for their current pregnancy (who are also reported under PMTCT_STAT) are reported under this modality. Refer to PMTCT_STAT reference sheet for guidelines on data collection. Individuals counted under PMTCT_STAT who already knew their status should not be reported under HTS_TST. f. PMTCT (Post ANC1: Pregnancy/L&D): Includes pregnant women who receive a first test or retest after ANC1 (“Post ANC1”), including women who are tested later in pregnancy (>ANC2) or during labor & delivery (L&D). g. PMTCT (Post ANC1: Breastfeeding): Includes women who receive a first test or retest after ANC1 (“Post ANC1”) while breastfeeding. If a woman is both pregnant and breastfeeding, she should be reported under PMTCT (Post ANC1: Pregnancy/L&D). h. STI: Includes persons seen in a designated STI clinic as well as patients seen in the OPD for STI symptoms. This includes suspect and confirmed STI cases.
